                        <h1><strong>FAQ: Cake Information</strong></h1>
                        <details>
                            <summary>
                                <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong>Why does my cake differ from the measurements?</strong></span></p>
                            </summary>
                            <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 14px;">The dimensions and weights of our cakes listed are approximates only and may vary slightly depending on the cake. Some cakes may shrink slightly during and/or after baking due to the nature of the ingredients, but were made using standardised cake pans relative to its size. &nbsp;</span></p>
                            <br>
                        </details>
                        <details>
                            <summary>
                                <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong>Why are there limited sizes for certain cakes?</strong></span></p>
                            </summary>
                            <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 14px;">The available sizes are set in order to achieve the best quality of the cake that is suitable for production.</span></p>
                            <br>
                        </details>
                        <details>
                            <summary>
                                <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong>How long can the cakes last at room temperature?</strong></span></p>
                            </summary>
                            <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Our cakes are prone to soften and melt after more than an hour unrefrigerated. It is recommended to keep our cakes chilled at all times and for at least 2 hours before serving.</span></p>
                            <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 14px;">The only exception is Moist Chocolate Cake, which is best served at room temperature or warmed (microwave 15 &ndash; 20 seconds).&nbsp;</span></p>
                            <br>
                        </details>
                        <details>
                            <summary>
                                <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong>Which cakes are suitable for longer periods without refrigeration?</strong></span></p>
                            </summary>
                            <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Our Moist Chocolate Cake is stable enough to maintain its shape even in room temperature, but not under direct sunlight. It is best served warmed (microwave 15 &ndash; 20 seconds) or at room temperature. This makes it a suitable choice for indoor celebrations or functions. Our brownies have similar properties as well.&nbsp;</span></p>
                            <br>
                        </details>
                        <details>
                            <summary>
                                <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong>How many days can I keep the cake in the refrigerator?</strong></span></p>
                            </summary>
                            <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 14px;">From the day of collection/delivery, our cakes can last up to 3 days in the refrigerator. It is best to keep the cake in an air-tight container to delay dehydration once cut. Chocolate Indulgence is best consumed on the same day.</span></p>
                            <br>
                        </details>
                        <details>
                            <summary>
                                <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong>Which of your cakes do not contain eggs?</strong></span></p>
                            </summary>
                            <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Our <a href="https://secretrecipe.com.sg/collections/eggless-cakes">eggless cakes</a> are <a href="https://secretrecipe.com.sg/products/oreo-cheese">Oreo Cheese</a>, and <a href="https://secretrecipe.com.sg/products/raspberry-cheese">Raspberry Cheese</a>. However, they are produced in the same facility as other cakes and may contain traces of eggs and/or other ingredients. The bases also comprise butter and biscuits that may contain eggs or traces of eggs. These cakes are not suitable for staunch lacto-vegetarians, ovo-vegetarians, vegans, or those avoiding allergic reactions. &nbsp;</span></p>
                            <br>
                        </details>
                        <details>
                            <summary>
                                <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong>Do you have cakes suitable for vegetarians?</strong></span></p>
                            </summary>
                            <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Most of our cakes contain butter and eggs, and some contain fish-based gelatin. All cakes are produced in the same facility as other cakes and may contain traces of other ingredients. Our cakes are generally not suitable for staunch vegetarians or those with allergic reactions to certain ingredients.</span></p>
                            <br>
                        </details>
                        <details>
                            <summary>
                                <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong>What is the type of gelatin used in Secret Recipe cakes? Which cakes do not contain gelatin?</strong></span></p>
                            </summary>
                            <p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 14px;">We use fish-based gelatin in our cakes containing gelatins.&nbsp;</span></p>
                            <div align="left" dir="ltr">
                                <table>
